article.headline: Northeastern 82, Stony Brook 63
article.story: BOSTON (AP) -- Marcus Barnes scored 26 points, 23 in the first half, to lead Northeastern to an 82-63 win over Stony Brook in the America East opener for both teams on Friday night. Jose Juan Barea added 18 points and eight assists for the Huskies (7-5, 1-0). Javorie Wilson added 13 points for Northeastern. Cori Spencer scored 23 points on 8-of-11 shooting to lead the Seawolves (3-7, 0-1), while D.J. Munir added 18 points. It was Stony Brook's fourth straight loss. Barnes made his first four shots, including three 3-pointers, as the Huskies jumped out to a quick 16-4 lead just 4:14 into the game. Stony Brook came back with a 10-5 run to cut the lead to 21-14 with 12:27 left in the first half, but Barnes remained hot as Northeastern took a 27-14 edge with 11:22 left in the first half. The Huskies led by as many as 18 in the first half and took a 45-30 lead at halftime. The Huskies maintained a 15-point lead through the first seven minutes of the second half and led 53-38 before putting the game away with an 11-0 run. Wilson had eight points in the surge, including a pair of 3-pointers and a layup to cap the run, which put Northeastern ahead 64-38 with 10:52 left. Northeastern eventually led by as much as 27, 69-42, before the Seawolves closed the gap late in the game.
